resources.string:
Signature versions for Android versions:
V1 - the first signature option, the only one up to Android 7.0;
V2 - added to Android 7.0;

The signature version should be used based on the minimum/target required Android version for the application. If the target version is 30+ (Android 11+), the V2 signature is required.

If you do not check the "Save" checkbox, then the selected schemes will be used only this time.

Signature versions for Android versions:
V1 – the first signature option, the only one up to Android 7.0;
V2 – added to Android 7.0;
V3 – added to Android 9.0;
V4 – added to Android 11;

The signature version should be used based on the minimum/target required Android version for the application. If the target version is 30+ (Android 11+), the V2 signature is required. V2 or V3 must be used together with the V4 signature. Version V4 is currently almost never used.

If you do not check the "Save" checkbox, then the selected schemes will be used only this time.
